ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa on Wednesday laid a wreath on the grave of  former ANC president Zaccheus Mahabane at the Seeisoville Cemetery in Kroonstad in the Free State. Accompanying him were newly elected ANC secretary-general Fikile Mbalula and second deputy secretary-general Maropene Ramokgopa, among others. The ceremony was part of the build-up to the ANC's 111th birthday celebrations on Sunday and was Ramaphosa's first public engagement since being re-elected for a second term as party president. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.